<l>kuṟṟeḻut timparu mōreḻuttu moḻikku</l>
<l>niṟṟal vēṇṭu mukarak kiḷavi</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> must occur [after <foreign xml:lang="ta">ū</foreign>] following after</l>
<l>the one-letter word and after a short-vowel [-word].<note place="foot">i.e., long monosyllabic open words in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ū</foreign> and disyllabic words with a preceding short syllable in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ū</foreign> will
          obtain the argument <foreign xml:lang="ta">u : tū + kuṟai &gt; tūukkuṟai ; uṭū + kuṟai &gt; uṭūukuṟai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
